&gt; Straight Shot looks to Leo as does Rattrap.  They had remembered something
&gt; Tucson had said to them.  Straight Shot walks beside Leo and puts a gentile
&gt; paw on his leg.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; Ya know, Tucson told us something that he wanted to tell you but never had
&gt; the chance to.  He told me that if he had the matrix in his hands, he would
&gt; not hesitate ta give it ta you, because he felt that even though he was
&gt; named a Prime, he felt that if anyone is worthy of the Matrix, it would be
&gt; you.  He told us he will always be committed to us but there was more to
&gt; being worthy of such an honor than just keeping promises.  There is so much
&gt; more that measures the worth of the Matrix bearer, and he felt he hasn&#39;t
&gt; quite lived up to that yet.  But he says you have more than proved your
&gt; worth .  He may try ta recover it but he promises it will be passed right to
&gt; you if he gets it somehow.&quot;

&lt;NEW&gt;

There was a nod from LEO PRIME, &quot;Prime is a title now, there are so
few who truely carry a shard of the matrix crystal anymore.&quot; There was
a small grim smile. &quot;The matrix still chooses its owners. Sometimes
that ownership is a wieght that many find difficult to carry.&quot;

As they arrived on the bridge, TORCA was alread rising from the
command chair, AIRHAMMER and BANTOR at the navigation and helm
consoles.

&quot;Ready for lift off.&quot; TORCA said.

LEO PRIME stood looking at the bridge for a moment and then nodded.
&quot;Lift off and send HYDRAS the coordinates to our landing point.&quot;

&quot;Yes sir.&quot; TORCA said as he turned to the others, &quot;Make it so.&quot;

LEO PRIME took his seat, motioning for STRAIGHT SHOT and the others to
take seats as well. Meanwhile the ship began to rumble as it slowly
began to move into the air.

